Step 1: Cook Brussels sprouts in boiling, lightly salted water until tender, about 7 minutes. Step 2: Meanwhile, melt Becel(R) Buttery Taste margarine in 12-inchnon-stick skillet over medium heat and cook shallot 6 minutes, stirring frequently, until golden and very soft. Add drained Brussels sprouts and stir to combine. Saute lightly until golden brown. Nutritional Facts Calories (Kcals): 170 % Daily Value Total Fat: 6g Saturated fat: 1g Trans Fat: 0g Polyunsaturates: 2.1g Omega-6: 1.4g Omega-3: 0.4g Monounsaturates: 2.8g 9% 5% Cholesterol:0mg 0% Sodium:100mg 4% Potassium: 977mg 22% Total Carbohydrate: 25g Dietary Fibre: 10g Sugars: 10g 8% 40% Protein: 8g Vitamin A: 15% Vitamin C: 330% Calcium: 10% Iron: 20% Preparation Time: 15 minutes Cook Time: 40 minutes Total time: 55 minutes http://www.becel.ca/en/becel/HeartHealthyRecipes/Side-Dishes/Browned-Buttery-Brussels-Sprouts.aspx